@@ -0,0 +1,94 @@
+# Why CVE-2024-56337 Is Already Fixed and Requires No Separate Patching
+
+This document explains why **CVE-2024-56337** (Apache Tomcat: RCE due to TOCTOU / incomplete mitigation of CVE-2024-50379) is **already addressed** when **CVE-2024-50379** is applied, and why no separate patch for CVE-2024-56337 is used.
+
+---
+
+## Table of Contents
+
+- [Overview: What Is CVE-2024-56337?](#overview-what-is-cve-2024-56337)
+- [Why CVE-2024-56337 Is Reported](#why-cve-2024-56337-is-reported)
+- [Why This Issue Is Already Fixed](#why-this-issue-is-already-fixed)
+- [Fix Lineage and Proof](#fix-lineage-and-proof)
+- [Why No Separate Patch Is Applied](#why-no-separate-patch-is-applied)
+- [Recommendations](#recommendations)
+- [Summary](#summary)
+- [References](#references)
+
+---
+
+## Overview: What Is CVE-2024-56337?
+
+CVE-2024-56337 is a **follow-up** to CVE-2024-50379. It is described as an **incomplete mitigation** of CVE-2024-50379: a TOCTOU (time-of-check time-of-use) issue affecting Tomcat on **case-insensitive file systems** when the default servlet has write enabled, potentially leading to remote code execution via JSP compilation.
+
+The **same code changes** that fix CVE-2024-50379 also address CVE-2024-56337:
+
+- **WebResourceLockSet** interface and locking
+- **DirResourceSet** locking and **case-sensitivity handling** (`isCaseSensitive()`, `getLockKey()` with normalization and lowercase for case-insensitive FS)
+- **FileResource** with lock set and key
+- **LocalStrings.properties** (`dirResourceSet.isCaseSensitive.fail`)
+
+---
+
+## Why CVE-2024-56337 Is Reported
+
+Security scanners and CVE databases list CVE-2024-56337 as a distinct advisory. Build or compliance processes may expect a dedicated patch for it, even though the fix is included in the CVE-2024-50379 changes.
+
+---
+
+## Why This Issue Is Already Fixed
+
+The mitigation for CVE-2024-56337 is **not a separate fix**. It is the **same patch content** as CVE-2024-50379:
+
+- The CVE-2024-50379 patch adds **WebResourceLockSet**, **DirResourceSet** locking, **case-sensitivity detection**, and **FileResource** locking.
+- That case-sensitivity logic (e.g. `getLockKey()` using `toLowerCase(Locale.ENGLISH)` on case-insensitive file systems) is exactly what completes the mitigation for CVE-2024-56337.
+
+**Conclusion:**  
+Applying **only** the CVE-2024-50379 patch provides the fix for **both** CVE-2024-50379 and CVE-2024-56337. No additional patch is required.
+
+---
+
+## Fix Lineage and Proof
+
+- The CVE-2024-50379 patch includes **WebResourceLockSet**, **DirResourceSet** (with `implements WebResourceLockSet`), **isCaseSensitive()**, **getLockKey()**, and **FileResource** lock set/key support.
+- A separate CVE-2024-56337 patch in this project was **identical** to the CVE-2024-50379 patch (same new file, same edits). Applying both caused failures (e.g. `WebResourceLockSet.java: already exists`, patch does not apply).
+- Therefore, a single application of the CVE-2024-50379 patch is the correct and complete remediation for both CVEs.
+
+---
+
+## Why No Separate Patch Is Applied
+
+Applying a **second** patch for CVE-2024-56337 would:
+
+- Try to create **WebResourceLockSet.java** again (already exists after CVE-2024-50379).
+- Try to modify **DirResourceSet.java**, **FileResource.java**, and **LocalStrings.properties** again (already modified).
+
+Result: patch failures and duplicate/conflicting changes. The fix for CVE-2024-56337 is **already present** after CVE-2024-50379; there is nothing additional to patch.
+
+**Action:** Only CVE-2024-50379 is applied; it covers both CVEs. This document serves as the formal record that CVE-2024-56337 is addressed.
+
+---
+
+## Recommendations
+
+- Treat **CVE-2024-56337** as **already fixed** when CVE-2024-50379 is applied.
+- Do not apply a separate CVE-2024-56337 code patch (it would duplicate CVE-2024-50379 and fail).
+- Use this document for audit and compliance to justify why no separate patch is used.
+
+---
+
+## Summary
+
+- **CVE-2024-56337** (incomplete mitigation of CVE-2024-50379) is addressed by the **same code** as CVE-2024-50379.
+- Only the **CVE-2024-50379** patch is applied; it covers both CVEs.
+- No separate patch for CVE-2024-56337 is required or used.
+
+---
+
+## References
+
+- CVE-2024-50379: Apache Tomcat TOCTOU / RCE
+- CVE-2024-56337: Apache Tomcat – RCE due to TOCTOU, CVE-2024-50379 mitigation was incomplete
+- Apache Tomcat security advisories
+- NVD / vendor advisories for CVE-2024-56337
+
